    "kicker": "Things to consider · before you commit",
    "title_html": "Three things <em>most</em> homeowners forget.",
    "items": [
      {
        "number": "01.",
        "heading": "Colonial Revival is the strictest style on this list when it comes to proportion.",
        "body": "Colonial Revival is the strictest style on this list when it comes to proportion. Asymmetry in the facade reads as 'wrong' immediately. If you are renovating, address window placement and entry symmetry before worrying about roof color. A perfect roof on an asymmetric colonial does not save the elevation."
      },
      {
        "number": "02.",
        "heading": "Charcoal is the safest mid-tone roof for resale.",
        "body": "Charcoal is the single most-installed asphalt color in the architectural category nationally, which means it appeals to the widest pool of resale buyers and translates across most home styles. If you are not strongly committed to a more decisive color (true black, weathered wood), charcoal is the lowest-risk choice."
      },
      {
        "number": "03.",
        "heading": "Install quality matters more than SKU.",
        "body": "All seven recommended SKUs hit Class A fire and 110-150 mph wind ratings. The bigger variable on a colonial elevation is install quality: ridge-line straightness, valley flashing, starter strip alignment. Insist on a Master Elite or equivalent certified contractor and a written workmanship warranty separate from the manufacturer's material warranty."
      }
    ]
